      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14.  ¶ Pterostylis curta ¶ , RBrown. ¶ 254.  ¶ Pterostylis reflexa ¶ , RBrown. ¶  ¶ I request sending several specimens of such plants whenever possible, because one or two are ruined in the dissectio...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">81.09.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">State Herbarium of South Australia, Plant Biodiversity Centre, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply 19.9.81'.</p>
               </note>14. <name key="Pterostylis%20curta">Pterostylis curta</name>, RBrown.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">254. <name key="Pterostylis%20reflexa">Pterostylis reflexa</name>, RBrown.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wenn immer es möglich, bitte ich mehrere Ex. von solchen Pflanzen zu senden, da 1 oder 2 in der Dissection (für Arten Ermittlung) zu Grunde gehen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">15 <name key="Sherardia%20arvensis">Sherardia arvensis</name> L.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>wenn ich die Pflanzen nach dem kürzlichen Exemplar richtig erkenne, und dann eingewandirt! Es ist keine Frucht daran.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihr Wohnort muss nahe dem Mt Lofty sein. Giebt es denn noch Baumfarne (<name key="Dicksonia%20Antarctica">Dicksonia Antarctica</name>) nahe dem 3ten Wasserfall (dem höchsten). Die Zahl der südaustr. Moose werden Sie verdoppeln können, da ich nie für längere Zeit selbst an dem vor 30 Jahren wenig zugänglichen Mt. Lofty sammeln konnte. Nur in Nebenszeit kann ich gelegentlich an Acacien arbeiten, u nehme Gruppe nach Gruppe vor, um mehreren Correspondenten gleichzeitig gerecht zu werden. Bei einer Artenzahl von 300 erfordert der Vergleich und die Durcharbeitung Vorsicht u <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">viel</hi>
               </seg> Zeit, die gerade nicht immer zu Gebot ist.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">12. <name key="Cladonia">Cladonia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">9. <name key="Fimbriaria">Fimbriaria</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(<name key="Claytonia%20calyptrata">Claytonia calyptrata</name> ist auch dabei)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich schreibe dies in später Nachtstunde und meine Augen versagen mir den Dienst, Cryptogamen zu erkennen. Je Tagsstunden sind der Departements Geschäfte — so viel, dass selten Zeit für Arbeiten dieser Art für befreundete Correspondenten überbleibt.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beunruhigen Sie sich wegen Ihres Nichterscheinens in der L.S. nicht; ich bin auch noch nie da gewesen, obgleich es 1/4 Jahrhundert her ist, wie mich Sir Will Hooker bat beizutreten.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit bestem Grusse, der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Vielleicht haben Sie Zeit in den Weihnachtsferien an der Encounter Bay zu sammeln.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Meine <name key="Banksia%20ornata">Banksia ornata</name> ist Ihnen nahe, bei Villunga, wenn nicht etwa durch das beständige Abbrennen der Gebüsche auch diese selten Pflanze zu Grunde ging. Würde ein Villunga Farmer für einen billigen Preis einen Korn-Sack voll der Früchte herbeischaffen, natürlich nicht von B. marginata.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">14/9/81</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">14. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Pterostylis%20curta">Pterostylis curta</name>
               </seg>, RBrown.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">254. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Pterostylis%20reflexa">Pterostylis reflexa</name>
               </seg>, RBrown.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I request sending several specimens of such plants whenever possible, because one or two are ruined in the dissection (for species research).</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">15 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Sherardia%20arvensis">Sherardia arvensis</name>
               </seg> L.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>if I recognize the plant from the recent specimen correctly, and then introduced! There is no fruit on it. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your home must be near Mt Lofty. Are there still tree ferns (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dicksonia antarctica</seg>) near the third waterfall (the highest). You will be able to double the number of South Australian mosses, because for a long time I could never collect on Mt Lofty which was less accessible 30 years ago. I can only occasionally work on <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s in spare time, and take up group after group in order to do justice to several correspondents at the same time. With a species number of 300, the comparison and working through requires care and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">much</hi>
               </seg> time, which is just not always available.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">12. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Cladonia">Cladonia</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">9. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Fimbriaria">Fimbriaria</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(<seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Claytonia%20calyptrata">Claytonia calyptrata</name>
               </seg> is also present)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am writing this in the late night hours and my eyes refuse to do me the service of recognizing cryptogams. Every hour of the day is the Department's business — so much that time rarely remains over for work of this kind for friendly correspondents.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do not be troubled about your non-appearance at the Linnean Society; I also have never been there, although it is a quarter of a century ago that Sir Will. Hooker asked me to join.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With best greetings your </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Perhaps you will have time in the Christmas holidays to collect at Encounter Bay. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Banksia%20ornata">Banksia ornata</name>
               </seg> is near you at Villunga,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Willunga, SA.</p>
               </note> unless perhaps these <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>rare plants are also destroyed by the constant burning of the bush. Would a Villunga farmer collect a corn sack full of the fruits for a cheap price, naturally not of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">B. marginata</seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>14/9/81</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
